like ""am I going to have a good time, or am I suddenly going to face a challenge that frustrates me for two hours?""Also on my list of annoyances are the puzzles. I spent two hours trying to solve a single puzzle last night. In the end, I caved and looked at a guide. The solution rather♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥me off, because it was the ONLY solution involving moving around 12 pieces. So, a puzzle that involves 12 pieces on a grid of let's say 40X80, to find the exact right way to place each piece, this wasn't fun. The room design for that puzzle also wasn't at all suggestive of a solution, which is something most good games with puzzles do, suggest a solution through the level design.You'd think with all my complaining, I'd not recommend this game, and in fact you'd be wrong.Regardless of its downfalls, things that I personally don't like, it's a really good game. As I mentioned above, the leveling is good (super grindy, but what did you expect from Secrets of Grindea), the skill system, the art style, the music, the item collection, crafting, story...All of it is done quite well.If you're into retro-styled RPGs, with very definite nods to the past, you'll probably like this one, even if it does make you feel stupid, from time to time."
