,Recommended,269770,22560192,"Posted: 21 April, 2016",all,Gary Baltimore,"I don't know what there is to say about this game that hasn't already been said. Despite its early access status, there is so much polish and attention to detail that, at a glance, it could pass as the finished product. I can tell the devs have put their hearts and souls into this game, and I'll be damned if it isn't paying off.If I had to give praise to anything, it would be the skills and perks available. Players aren't locked into classes, so they have complete control over how their character develops and the niche they fill in battle. For instance, one-handed melee skills that deal multiple hits in one use benefit greatly from perks that improve critital hits. Then, tack on a movement speed bonus for charging skills or blocking with your shield, and you've built an acrobat that hits fast and hits hard.Of course, there are so many other praises I could sing -- the cheeky jabs at RPG tropes, the deliciously roguelike arcade mode, the atmospheric and memorable soundtrack, -- but words can only do it so much justice. If you're on the fence about this game, do yourself a favor and try the demo. Pixel Ferrets, have yourselves a cup of coffee, on me."
