76561198025060095,Recommended,269770,18112915,"Posted: 20 September, 2015",all,Sose,"Played this game with 2 friends, story mode on hard difficulty was definitely challenging, especially some of the boss fights require multiple attempts, forcing you to learn the patterns instead of just smashing buttons.Some of the level design reminds me of Legend of Zelda, combat brought back memories of Secret of Mana and brutal (but fair) boss design could be compared to games like Ys.The game has ""grind"" in its name so if you're a fan of hunting for items, it certainly has that aspect aswell. There's really no reason to grind if you don't feel like it. The grinding aspect works well though, the longer you stay in one area and the more enemies you kill, the faster they start spawning with some of them being stronger ""elite"" versions of normal enemies. So the difficulty starts ramping up and it can get pretty chaotic after a short while.Lots of fun with friends, just be aware that it is early access - not all of the game zones or skills are implemented but the core gameplay and mechanics are solid already.We've yet to finish the story mode and we haven't tried arcade mode yet. But I can already recommend it, atleast as a co-op game if you're fans of ARPGs."
