76561198036248595,Recommended,269770,17141151,"Posted: 20 July, 2015",all,LastChime,"TL/DR;Pros- Spiritual successor to older ARPG titles (Secret of Mana/Star Tropics/A Link to the Past)- Solid build customization and choices that change gameplay a lot- Responsive Controls, Xbox controller works fine off the hop with zero third party software necessary- Good Humor- Good Multiplayer Experience and Customization- Decent Musical Score- Fairly difficult compared to modern games (Tough but fair, it's not quite ""Nintendo Hard"" but close)Cons- Default keybindings can be hard on hands, probably want a controller unless you want to custom keybind.- Menu slightly unintuitive at first- Crafting doesn't seem to be covered at all in the first few hours or so- Game is incomplete, some areas not accessable even early on, does not impact current gameplay though.It's pretty decent, only have 3 hours in so far though.Like it says on the tin it definitely captures the spirit of Secret of Mana/A Link to the Past/Star Tropics. However it also adds in some nice new shiny features, the biggest one being build customization. I guess the closest comparison on the build system would be something like Skyrim or Kingdoms of Amular: Reckoning (as in non linear, pick whatever you want but there's still progression within each).The controls are responsive however being an old goat I got hand cramps after the first hour and switched to Xbox 360 controller and enjoyed it a lot more after that (could still probably be solved with some manual rebinding). It's a little quirky to get used to the menu controls being that it behaves exactly like an old SNES title (no mouse, nested menus button press down and back up).The dialogue is pretty funny, it has a lot of fourth wall humor often poking fun at itself and the genre. So far the score is decent but I'm only a few hours in.I got a few friends to buy it and we've been playing together and having a blast, the steam integration makes this super easy. You can choose whether to scale the leveling or not which seems nice but hasn't actually been tested by me yet, we're all pretty low level so I didn't see the point. Also loot options can be customized I didn't bother though as round robin seemed to work, the nice thing is it seems that if you haven't got a chest yet in story mode and another player opens it up you still get it. It doesn't seem to scale the enemies much in 2 player, so you can sort of cheese some content by ressurecting a downed player, but you have to time it properly so I guess it's not the end of the world. Oh and other than that, there's no healing in the game beyond picking up a certain drop (sort of like old Mega-Man games).I was nervous buying on early access but feel that this genre was worth the investment, we don't see many and I was pleasently suprised by the quality of this early access and the decent amount of difficulty in the game, you'll probably die quite a bit, but it's pretty fair. So yeah would recommend.EDIT: After playing with 3 the difficulty does indeed scale, though perhaps not enough I removed the con from the list."
