76561198021794395,Recommended,269770,18623237,"Posted: 22 October, 2015",all,Furry,"Excellent action rpg. Like a cross between Ys and Zelda. Very good gameplay 10/10. The combat mechanics are very well thought out, many enemies cooperate and you have to plan your attacks accordingly. Bosses will make your heart race, some of them reminds a bit of bullet hell shooters. Animations are very nicely done, music is good. Story seems pretty standard for this kind of game so far, not exactly Chrono Trigger level, but its engaging enough to want to know what happens next and theres lots of funny moments. Theres a simple fishing minigame, mainly for providing food to your pets, who gives different permanent buffs depending on what you feed them, and some not so hard puzzles.I dunno how much of the game (story mode) is finished atm, mabye 1/4? (hope its less :p ) The content that is in the game seems 100% done and everything is working great, very polished, unlike most early access games... Didnt notice any bugs. As of now theres about 10-12 hours worth of the main game (mabye a bit less if you play on normal and just blaze through) + xx hours of arcade mode, wich is a sort of semi random series of ""rooms"" where you try to get as far as possible before you die while building up your character on the way, and get your high score in the global ranking, great fun. Havent tried it in co-op mode yet so cant comment on that.I can confidently recomend this to anyone, any age, who likes this sort of game. Its a good challenge on hard. Again, the combat gameplay is great, you have to time it right and use the shield, reflect projectiles and know when to go all out and when to hold back. Truly a gem in the making."
