76561197986748757,Recommended,269770,19445425,"Posted: 2 December, 2015",all,Lucien,"I agree with many other reviewers beneath me in that Grindea is an engaging, bugless and smooth rpg that has a definite MMORPG feel with the optional rare items farming that I find incredibly relaxing.Pros -*Excellent 2-D graphics without being pixelated as seems to be the norm lately.*Responsive easy to learn controls that forgive mistakes but only to a point.*Crafting system makes even weak monsters seem worth killing.*Boss fights are genuinely epic and satisfying.Cons -*Crafting system starts out promising but the lack of items to make in later levels makes it feel gimmicky instead.*Lack of weapons in general makes battles feel too repetitive after awhile.*Replay value somewhat hindered in storymode by the increasing costs of changing your talent points, sometimes requiring 30 minutes to an hour of farming to try something new.All in all I'd say for an early access game this is terrific and if the developers could fix the above issues and perhaps double what is already in the beginning stages...It would be a good I would be willing to pay 40+ dollars for. It feels like an offline MMORPG with Zelda-esque vibes. Great game for relaxing and listening to tunes. I pray it gets better from here."
