,Recommended,269770,17129943,"Posted: 19 July, 2015",all,snigg,"I got a little frustrated while exploring when I first got this game, as I discovered the second half of the story mode wasn't completed yet, but this is an early access game with ACTIVE devs who are constantly working on the game to make it the best it can be. The gameplay is very intuitive and fun, and the story is great. You are a collector, and you explore the world looking for cool loot, when you discover that you bag is a living artifact, created long ago, and he's not the only one. In the temples of this game, you must get the artifact at the end, and it seems repetitive, but the game has different ways of getting you into the temple, and (of the two that are in the game currently) each temple has it's own gimmick that makes it stand out from the other(s).If you finish the story as it is now, there is an alternate mode which has more of a Binding of Issac gameplay style as you go through randomly generated floors and fight monsters and attain treasure. But there's a twist; As you progress and earn points through playing Arcade mode, your town upgrades and you can do different things in the town.None of my friends have this game so I haven't gotten to play multiplayer, but if it's as good as single player, I'll love it.Basically, this game has no class restrictions, so you're allowed to grab whatever spells you want, as long as you have skill points, which I absolutely LOVE. This makes chaining spells with your melee attacks incredibly fun and rewarding, but one con I have with this game is that some spells aren't in the game yet.Buy this game if you have the patience to wait until ths game reaches its full potential."
