76561198085587451,Recommended,269770,17740149,"Posted: 27 August, 2015",all,Nesdude,"**This review is coming from a pure single-player experience** (there is multiplayer)I have done all of the story mode content there is to do at this time, minus collectibles, as of version 0.600amigo.Pros:-Fun combat, lots of skills and perks. You can respec for a doable in-game fee. Smooth and fluid animation.-Multiplayer, which I did not try out. This can be done in the story mode and arcade mode.-The environments are awesome, the character artwork could be better, and the music is good, but nothing I see myself humming to.-Many cameos from other video games. Zelda, RE4, Honeydew, to name a few.-There's a stable version and a ""frontline"" version. Pretty self explanatory. The latter has more frequent updates (every few weeks) the former every month or two, from my understanding.Cons:-The amount of monsters you have to kill and the many hours it takes to get a drop does not line up with an items rarity most of the time. It is not unheard of to spend 4-8 hours killing the same monster all to get a drop that is probably not better than what you already have JUST so you can work towards 100% completion. This is never a requirement, but the cards you can get in particular offer small permanent bonuses, and it can take you anywhere from 30 minutes to 8 hours to find the one that you want.-It's short. But the game's not done yet. The current story can be done in about 4-6 hours. Getting collectibles could get you another 10-20 hours, depending on your luck. Question is, do you want those mostly mediocre drops bad enough to spend all that time?-Arcade mode as a single player is quite a challenge. I usually opt for the harder options in video games like Kingdom Hearts on Critical but this mode is hard from the get go if you are alone. I would like to see some scaling in difficulty to make it more doable (maybe there already is, and I just suck.) But if you're looking for a challenge, you've got it here. An option to turn down the difficulty would be nice though.These problems can be easily remedied with time, however. The creators are friendly and interactive with their community, and they post frequent updates.So the question is, do I recommend this game? Is it worth the current price of $15.00?Yes it is. For the amount of playtime I got out of it, for the potential of what it can become, and for the multiplayer, which I didn't even touch, which is sure to add many hours. If nothing else, follow this game. Come back to it later. For an avid RPG fan, this is a game to watch out for."
