,Recommended,269770,17230080,"Posted: 25 July, 2015",all,Pharticus Maximus,"This is what indie retro games is all about. Forget all those games you get in bundles that claim to be retro greatness, but they are really just posing behind 8 & 16 bit graphics but are missing all the greatness that those eras stood for. Those games try to make you buy their games based on your love for nostalgia. This one hit it on the money!!!!!Secrets of Grindea!!!! Oh yes, this game has done it all right. This is a game that brings back all the best memories from the classic era, games like Zelda for SNES, Secrets of Mana, and it takes what we loved in those games to a whole new level with modern additions and systems.The combat is awesome action RPG goodness. Hack and slash, cast spells, dodge, block, aim, it is all here and feels great, tight and responsive.The class system is that you can be anything you want. use any weapon, buy any skill from any school of magic. Boost defense, boost elements, boost crit, boost certain spell types and so on. Insane amount of depth with limitless combination of ways to build your character.You can also customize the way you look with different looking hats, shields, weapons that you find and equip throughout the game, its all visible, your hair and skin color and more is also selectable.Slash bushes, crates, vases, you know we all loved to do that and see what item is inside, could be nothing or something great.There is crafting, fishing and all kinds of other ""jobs"" that you can do in this game as well. It has multiplayer where friends can join you on your adventure online.This game has so much greatness and is only in EA. These Devs work hard and love what they are creating and it shows. If you really love retro gaming, you will buy this now!!! Stop buying the low quality crap that comes from greenlight for 10 games in a $1 bundle and put your cash down on something you will actually play, enjoy and be proud to own and say you paid for."
