76561198044420302,Recommended,269770,19140854,"Posted: 17 November, 2015",all,Mullic Rav,"Okay, so my time says 2.2 hours, mostly for the case because it does'nt count offline time... BUT i still think being that i've gotten pretty dang far, i think i should have a say, before i start, these are simply my pros and cons upon the game, you like them, great! if not, well prefernaces are preferances! now let's get started!Pros:-Old fashion RPG style, i think it's refreshing to see old styles coming back, not lazily done either, this was actually made as such with care, sure it's a work in progress or ""Early Access"", BUT so far, can't complain too much about the game style.-graphic style, i'm not usually one for 2d pixle style unless it's either done well, or turns out like terraria, where the gameplay makes up for it (My opinion... besides, you can make you're own texture packs for terraria anyways...), but game however, has done it correctly in my opinion, given it that charm that i don't get from most games now a days.-skills, sure alot of them are'nt that ""Uniqe"", but they are pretty good, concidering you can dash foward and damage anything in the way? or leap back and slash foward? i can't complain that much!-Cards, this is actually better then you may think, No it's not part of a card game, but their permanent boost to a certain stat, or additional damage or special ability, plenty a pain to gain, but pretty good otherwise.-Crafting, not much at the moment, but i can see this going pretty well if done well.-Costume slot, Has to be said, considering i can have a full plate helm and still look like i just have glasses on, basically making my own appearance in the game? gotta say, THIS i really like...-Pets, Gotta say, i like pet's as is, but just having a jack o lantern as an option? that won me over for that detail, but to the real stuff, basically feeding you're pets, you give the xp in a certain stat, once it levels, it gives you a bonus for as long as you have the pet! (Seriosely though, Devs, Great job on the jumpkin pet, Love it, Love it, LOVE, IT...)now the cons (Note: i don't have too many because the rest are mostly one nuetrals):-YES the game is very grind-ish at times, gaining materials, certain armors, weapons, I'm just placing this here because even I have to admit that this CAN get mind numbing, BUT take note: This one is least concerning, why? The word ""Grind"" is in the title, so really... well that IS what you're getting a peice of... but to be fair, you don't HAVE to grind to get through the story, again, don't pay TOO much attention to this one.Now the Nuetrals:_Custimization: Yes i do like the costume feature, and yes i can basically make myself in real rife... for the most part, still missing facial hair, but we are playing as a young child... my point in this one is, Yes it's there, just not much of it is there at this time, which the reason it's a nuetral? ""Early access"" is why.-Armor, and when i say this one, i mostly mean chest armor appearance, basxically... it never changes, no form of changing it accept colors, i guess you could say this is SORT of a request, but a deal breaker by any means, Just a small request to let us change from simple shirt and scarf to say leather or metal armor? to appropriate to the class? robesx for mages, leather for rogues, metal for tanks? mostly for appearance, like in costumes...-Difficulty, i don't mean for the common enemies, i just mean for certain bosses it CAN be rather... unforgiving... until you find some form of work around or loopole to the boss...That's about it really, again, the game is early access, so not TOO much can be said upon it quite yet, it does look promising so far, heck, if i had friends or people to play with, or someone to help get through the story, i'de go for i9t to be honest, but any ways,  at the current time, i would give this game... 7.5/10 seem fair? for it's current status, this is in no way the final grade, but yeah for those who just want a charming, nice, Mostly friendly game to play, i recommend this plenty!"
