,Recommended,269770,19072853,"Posted: 14 November, 2015",all,Nandaba,"Game is amazing. It plays like a Legend of Zelda/Terranigma sort of classic ARPG. The story and characters aren't super compelling, but are good enough to keep you involved in the game and not detract from the gameplay. Your talking item bag sidekick is great, though. The music is amazing. The combat system and level-up systems are great, there's a lot of customizability for how you choose to play the game. Lots of the options for combat have great synergy between them, and there are no class restrictions to skills, creating a sort of mix-and-match build system that feels really fun.The only negative disclaimer is that the game definitely isn't finished yet. The content runs out 5-7 hours into the game right now, smack in the middle of the plot. If unfinished content isn't your thing, I would recommend waiting for the game to be completed before buying."
