76561198004785234,Recommended,269770,22725758,"Posted: 30 April, 2016",all,Jhonario,"I will preface this by saying I JUST started playing the game to determine my first impressions about the gameplay.  I did this on purpose so that I wouldn't be distracted by all the fluff in this game.  There is, as you can already see, a very pleasant and deliberate art style.  It's inspired, of course, by the tested and established Zelda franchise.  The gameplay also feels a lot like Zelda.  There are other inspirations from SNES-era RPGs, of course, but this is the most salient to talk about - and I'll explain why.When I say that this game feels like Zelda, I mean that in that it's both limiting and pleasant.  The walking speed is just about the perfect speed to be neither too fast or too slow - it's just pleasant.  The attack length is neither too much or too little - it's just pleasant.  At the same time, Grindea suffers from the same sort of creative stagnation that Zelda's combat had.  There's about 8 types of swords, 8 types of 2-handed swords, 1 bow to my knowledge (really, devs?).  To be fair, this is about the same level of variance that Link To The Past had in it's weapon variety.  But, if you're expecting a modern pc merging of Zelda swordplay and Diablo lootgrabbing, you will not find it here.  There's plenty of the former, none of the latter.  Even Secret of Mana - which you're undoubtedly going to compare this game to - had a more robust combat system where you had to time weapon swings and charge attacks... AND YOU HAD DIFFERENT WEAPONS BESIDES SWORDS!!I want to be clear, though:  I am enjoying this game.  I'm going to be playing it.  It's too early to tell how good the skill tree is - but I can already tell that levelling up is EXTREMELY satisfying and rewarding.  There is huge potential in this game.  I just really hope that the devs can stop being held behind by LoZ:LTTP and just let their imaginations go - or that the fluff and story make this game worth it."
76561198153436037,Recommended,269770,22709374,"Posted: 29 April, 2016",all,Cindy,"I have no life because of this game, I need MOAR.WHEN IS THE GAME COMING OUT, I AM SITTING HERE DOING NOTHING.xoxoxo-Cindy"
,Recommended,269770,22653989,"Posted: 26 April, 2016",all,GamingWolf,"Secrets of Grindea is an RPG with real time combat like Zelda,and is fun to play with or without a friend,which is really rare on RPG with MP games.Pros:*No class restrictions (you can be a fire mage with a cloud and a ice friend protecting you,i'm serious)*Puzzles,LOADS of puzzles,and you will need some time to think about some.*Character creation,not much to talk about here,move along.*Regions. They can vary from a city to a spoopy forest,and they are all fun!*Combat,mixing skills,making awesome combos,and crafting another weapon to be stronger,REPEAT!*Pixel art is great!*The Story. The characters are lovable,and with time you will change your opinion about some,also,there's some plot twists here,funny jokes there,and TONS of sarcasm.*Cards,or Monster Cards if you like,are rare drops from enemies,if you got a card from a enemy,it will give you a random bonus and a cute artwork from the enemy you killed,which is ALWAYS a plus in my book.*Soundtrack is good*Balanced (at least on normal mode),like the Yetis are MADE to tank your attacks,and some other enemies are made to be annoying.*Easy to connect to MP through Steam and AWSOME controller support.*THE EASTER EGGS!!!!!! I managed to find a Triforce near the pile of gold in the flashback sequence!!!! :D*You can replay bosses to get more loot from them,well,everyone but...Cons:*You can't replay Winter's or the Mt. Bloom boss fights,I mean,the Winter boss was one of the most fun boss battles I ever saw,even if it didn't drop ANY loot,I would be playing it for ages,not for the Mt. Bloom boss fights,but they could have some extra loot and the replay feature anyway :|*GRINDING,and i'm not a fan of it.It's not just walking in circles to begin a battle,you have to kill ALL enemies in the room to spawn another wave of enemies,although this sistem is great,it's boring to get the action going.*The crafting system could be improved,like seeing the item kinda 