,Recommended,269770,22784679,"Posted: 3 May, 2016",all,Dadraina,"Absolutely love this game. I wasn't sure, at first, if I would like it though. But once I started playing? I can't stop! I keep creating new characters so I can start fresh when I get my friends to start playing. Been telling people all about it! So ready for more to come out, but understand that it takes time. I'm just so impatient!!! Noticed a few minor glitches/issues, but completely understandable due to being in beta still. If you are joining someone else's game, you have to from the get-go (meaning: before they even start their game: thus at the invite screen when hosting a game). You can not jump in mid-game or there will be issues (screen freezing, health bar stretching across screen, screen resolution messed up, major lag, unable to charge powers, etc). Also, if you are joining a game and you are fighting monsters from/or in the Haunted Forest, you get X and Y (what look like coordinates) in your text/chat box. A little upset over the chances of getting a card, but that makes me play the game more TO get cards. Overall though, I HIGHLY recommend this game for others. It may be in beta, but with the amount of game play time and the story line/plot and just how much fun it is... it's totally worth it! Please! If you're even CONSIDERING buying this game, please do! It's worth it, I promise! Plus, the more people buy the beta, the better it helps the developers/builders of this game. GO PIXEL FERRETS!!!!"
