,Recommended,269770,27956960,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,Sean777o,"This game is very promising. It may be early access but don't let that deter you as it has tons of content to keep you interested. If you're a fan of games like Final Fantasy, the Legend of Zelda, Fantasy Life or other similar RPG games you'll find joy here. The 4th Wall is something it likes to smash down quite often as you'll come across many Easter Eggs and reference, one being the Triforce laying on the ground or a character mentioning ""/"" commands. Secrets of Grindea knows it's a video game and uses that to it's pleasure since it allows it to make tons of jokes. Heck you start out from a town called ""Startington"".The characters are also quite pleasing to meet. Your father has a backstory and a driving motive that I find interesting to explore, as you plung further into the game his past is opened up to a point where you realize you aren't the only character of importance running around Grindea. The games controls seemed odd to me at first but I later came to admire how well they work. The arrow keys act as your movement while Z & X are your sword and shield. You have items and skills linked to the A,S,D,F,G,Q,W,E,R,T keys which can each be rebinded. I tried to change them around but I find it much more comfortable to use the defaults.I definitely recommend this game to any fans of RPGs and in-game collecting."
76561198022290902,Recommended,269770,27639728,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,Sandan,"Secrets of Grindea is a promising one in the category of early access games. It's got lovely art, good controls and a solid story that doesn't take itself too seriously. In terms of gameplay, a comparison to secret of mana seems fair: The fights are very dynamic, you can always move around freely during the fights. As your character progresses, you learn new spells and attacks which you can select with a buttons press from your quick-slots mid-fight. Attacks can also be charged.There is a fairly standard equipment system.Aside of the main storyline, a lot of NPCs will ask you for help in various ways.The strongest point of this game has to be, undoubtedly, the multiplayer support. Playing the campain with a couple of friends gives off a really well-crafted feel. The arcade-mode can also be played with friends.The creators of the game maintain a devlog on the games homepage. So far, there is a lot of activity on there."
