,Recommended,269770,22439023,"Posted: 15 April, 2016",all,harloweshannon,"Great game, though unfinished (obviously). I've put 6 hours into it and I'm at 33% completed. No matter, they've done quite a bit with what seems like a simple interface and mechanics.The animations are excellent, the bosses are tough, and there's enough to the leveling system to keep you interested, though it's not incredibly deep.  The maps aren't huge, but I'm not sure if this really works against the game. It says what it is right there in the title, and you don't need endlessly huge maps to grind endlessly spawning mobs. The story is mostly cliched/cheesy but it's hard to write a good story that isn't, these days, without it just being absurd or abstract, and besides--you don't play a game like this for the story. There's enough cartooniness and action to make it all work.Overall, worth it!"
