,Recommended,269770,20654546,"Posted: 20 January, 2016",all,DParse,"This game is excellent but suffers some problems.Secrets of Grindea is a Zelda style action RPG with levelling.Edit: Originally I had a paragraph here stating that the game is way too hard, but then I learned that I set the game to ""hard"" when I started - so to complain about that would be dumb :P. The next paragraph still stands though, regarding some of the hard parts of the game.I think this could be remedied with a pretty simple fix - another branch of magic that lets you heal/buff. The game has no health potions, so you're at the mercy of health drops from enemies.Also, it suffers from a lack of content. This isn't a hard negative - it's still in early access! From the looks of things, the developers have a ton of content planned. As far as I've gotten though, there are very few side quests or optional dungeons, and not a lot of equipment variety.Probably the most disappointing thing is that, after I started a multiplayer playthrough with my friend, we don't both get Monster Cards together. Loot in general is shared evenly (in Round-Robin sharing) but monster cards take so long to get that it is very very disheartening to not get one when it drops and your friend gets it.My last negative point  - the soundtrack is only mediocre. Lots of games these days have phenomenal soundtracks, so you almost expect it when a game hits ""Overwhelmingly Positive"". I think this game can get there - but the soundtrack isn't helping. It's not bad, but it's not good enough.But the positives. Oh man, I could go on and on. So I will.The first thing is the graphics - it's BEAUTIFUL. Some of the best pixel art I've seen in years.  Your avatar can be customized with a ton of different styles and colors, and they all look great. Every enemy and character is gorgeously animated . The environment is amazing. This game is just overflowing with great visuals.The gameplay is a TON of fun. Combat is great with a few snags in my opinion. The skill system lets you pick whatever skills you want first, with 4 different magic elements and physical skills to choose from. There's a good amount of variety in builds and if you have (quite a lot of) money you can respec all your skills. You can stagger enemies and get bonuses from precise shield blocking. Sometimes if you attack too quickly, it eats your input and you just stand there, so that can be pretty annoying.You have a bottomless bag (No inventory management! 5 Stars right there). Enemies drop stuff ALL THE TIME and its really satisfying to collect it all. And there's a ton of stuff to collect. It's a grind-lovers dream. You can refight bosses to get their rare drops.  Every enemy in the game has an ULTRA-RARE drop as well, which can be fun to farm for.There's a crafting system that lets you build new equipment with all the drops you collect. IMO the game needs more mage equipment - I still only have 1 wand, from the beginning of the game.There are so manywell-donemechanics in this game - collecting things is a blast, refighting bosses is excellent, there is a challenge arena, good variety of enemies. It's a ton of fun to play and I can't wait for the full version to come out.All in all, I highly recommend this game to anyone that likes RPGs or the Legend Of Zelda series."
