,Recommended,269770,20865718,"Posted: 30 January, 2016",all,Fuzzy_Dice,"I found this game a little while ago on some out of the way site and I really liked it, even though it wasn't developed past the introductory first boss battle. When I found it here, I was pleasantly surprised and immediately was interested, thinking ""I wonder how much has happened when I wasn't looking."" What I found was 8 or so new bosses and a ton more background and detail. I bought the game, already half knowing what to expect, and my idea that this game was a good one was reaffirmed by the update. It's a good game, with puns and lines that make you kind of cringe in the way of, ""Oh why would you say that? That's just...no, just...no."" The gameplay is good too, with a unique playstyle that I haven't heard of before (though, that's not saying much), and a nice little challenge that you could spend some spare time doing when you are looking for a nice adventure. The bosses are various, and, in some cases (*cough* Winter *cough*cough*), the bosses take quite a few lives and not a little amount of patience. The characters are unique and have a little bit of background, and if you are expecting some dark twist, then you will be disappointed. Some of the advanced mechanics are a little troublesome, but they come with time and practice. You will also eventually have to learn how to cluster enemies or just plain run away to get breathing space, as enemies are prone to try to trap you, or just plain overwhelm you. However, in the end, it's a game in progress, like so many great things once started as, and has started off beautifully, and will hopefully grow and flourish into something worthy of praise and awe like so many games out there, like Undertale, or Minecraft, to name a few. If a few of you do not match my opinions, that is fine, everyone is entitled. Anyways, I recommend this game, as it will go far, and if you blink, you might just miss its growth to success."
