76561198076333546,Recommended,269770,23009922,"Posted: 15 May, 2016",all,Elsien,"Secrets of Grindea is an amazing experience single player, and even more fun with a friend... or 3!With a playstyle similar to The Legend of Zelda: A link to the Past for SNES, the game is familliar to old school gamers. The aestetic appeals to a wide variety of gamers young and old. The gameplay is fun, very addicting, and will have you trying different character builds, and *Grindeaing* for every item, card, and achievment in the game!Story mode is fun and with amusing and quirky dialog at times.The highlight of this game, and the greatest challenge, is the Arcade mode - where you try and compete for the top single run score in the world by adventuring through room after room, floor after floor where the environment, monsters, and bosses reflect the story mode progression. This is no easy task, and will have you coming back run after run to upgrade your camp and gain more perks to give you the edge you will need to reach #1!!All in all, if you like simplistic action rpgs with puzzles and rewarding combat prowess, then just BUY this game.The best part is that at the time of this review - the game is still in beta and is not even fully complete - but still worth every single penny, and then some!"
