76561198125462961,Recommended,269770,24703131,"Posted: 3 August, 2016",all,My Beard Holds Muh Lunch,"Well, I picked this up thinking, I have some time off and don't want to get too involved in anything and this seems like it could fit the niche.  I'm not positive how far into the game I currently am but it's been about 5 hours of entertainment ( i've actually been more entertained in the past 5 hours than almost my entire play through of Fallout 4).The ""STORY"" my gaming jesus  so far the little tid bits of what i'll call lore for now, are spaced well and very attractive to anyone who likes story heavy games.  The way the story is being told and the humor is very satisfying.  Giving you enough slack to enjoy bashing in enemies faces while at the same time being 100% ready to get right back into whichever quest you were up to when you decided to stop and ""grindea"" few levels out ;D .The ""ART STYLE"" is fairly simple and ""old school"" classic indie.  I can't complain though considering it allows all varieties of computers to play it aswell as not degrading the quality of the gameplay itself.  They also do a decent job at making the variants of objects reasonably refreshing in their surroundings.The ""COMBAT MECHANICS"" aren't overwhelming, timing is key, patterns exist in most cases (which typically require a decent amount of focus to manipulate). Although the spell casting can be very frustrating with keybind locations.  Personally I would avoid a heavy attack magic play (unless they format it to work more effectivly in the final game).  Overall it feels pretty fluid.The ""CHARACTERS"" some of them are steriotypical but they fill the rolls they hold very well and give most players a comfortable feeling from the homefront foward.  Some of them (so far) have had decent story driven developement and I look foward to finishing the game to see their full fruiting when I can finish this game.""OVERALL"" So far i'll give this game a solid 7.6/10 (For it's genre and from a single player only unfinished playthrough experience).  It is, however, still in Beta.  Meaning the More people who try this game (and hopefully enjoy it) will give it the opprotunity to finish developement at a reasonable pace and fund the developers.*SUBNOTES-I don't usually bother writing reviews since they can be a dime a dozen with most overly hyped games or just mass playerbase games that I commonly find myself playing to pass time.  I apologize if my format isn't visually pleasing, if I made any spelling/grammar mistakes, or if it wasn't in depth enough to make you atleast want to try the game (though you seriously should atleast look into trying it c: )."
