,Recommended,269770,28977907,Posted: 3 January,all,Sluice Master,"A very polished little ARPG, especially for Early Access. This is probably the closest I've felt to playing Four Swords Adventures or Crystal Chronicles with friends in years.Pros:- Fun Secret of Mana-style combat that rewards smart positioning and timing.- Totally customizable skills and passive talents (no classes, get any ability you want) that let you really play any way.- Perfectly functional online co-op that works over Steam or direct IP.- Character-based saves: Play in single-player, then take your character online to do stuff with friends!- Neat little sidequests for exploring or doing puzzles, and an arena with its own rewards.- Lots of items to craft and buy for different play types.- Boss fights with unique mechanics that'll kill you over and over until you get gud.- Cute music that gets stuck in your head.- Nice sprite art that doesn't feel like a cheap way to make graphics. Animations look real good.- Light tongue-in-cheek story and dialogue that isn't blunt enough to be annoying or cringey.- Arcade ""roguelike"" mode for when you just wanna chill and fight stuff with friends.Cons:- Facing in one direction is sometimes finicky; I've gotten hit often because my shield was up in the wrong place.- No local co-op, only online. Online is awesome, but there's something special about local that it can't do.- The game art is good, but character portraits look like Babby's First deviantART Submission.- Slow and somewhat confusing menus: It takes more time and more button presses than I'd like in order to change equipment or use skill points. There are quick-swap and quick-level features to help, but they're only for when you get a new item or when you've just leveled up, and they don't help when you wanna switch to equipment you already have or level something new.- Not all skills are in the game yet: There's a good range of one-handed, two-handed, and magical skills, but only two for support so far.- Unfinished areas and features: Trying to go in certain directions or use certain options gives you a text box that says that that thing isn't in the game yet. This is only a chunk of the final game's world.- Very rare crashes: I've encountered one crash so far. It was in a cut-scene where I was supposed to get a unique item, and since the host got the item fine, I had to go back and play the section in single-player to get it for my character. It really wasn't a big deal, but there might be more crashes that I'm not aware of.Basically, the worst thing about this game is that they're still making more of it."
